From (H2653) chophaph (in the moral sense of covered from soil); pure -- innocent. see HEBREW (H2653) chophaph
An orthographical variation of (H2645) chaphah; properly, to cover, i.e. (in a sinister sense) to act covertly -- do secretly. see HEBREW (H2645) chaphah
A primitive root (compare (H2644) chapha', (H2653) chophaph); to cover; by implication, to veil, to encase, protect -- ceil, cover, overlay. see HEBREW (H2644) chapha' see HEBREW (H2653) chophaph
From (H2645) chaphah; a canopy -- chamber, closet, defence. see HEBREW (H2645) chaphah
The same as (H2646) chuppah; Chuppah, an Israelite -- Huppah. see HEBREW (H2646) chuppah

column7: to be in trepidation, hurry or alarm
column9: A primitive root; properly, to start up suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, to fear -- (make) haste (away), tremble.
From (H2468) Chuldah; hasty flight -- haste. see HEBREW (H2468) Chuldah
Plural of (H2646) chuppah (compare (H2349) Chuwpham); Chuppim, an Israelite -- Huppim. see HEBREW (H2646) chuppah see HEBREW (H2349) Chuwpham
From an unused root of uncertain signification; a fist (only in the dual) -- fists, (both) hands, hand(-ful).
From (H2651) chophen; perhaps pugilist; Chophni, an Israelite -- Hophni. see HEBREW (H2651) chophen
A primitive root (compare (H2645) chaphah, (H3182) yacheph); to cover (in protection) -- cover. see HEBREW (H2645) chaphah see HEBREW (H3182) yacheph

A primitive root; properly, to incline to; by implication (literally but rarely) to bend; figuratively, to be pleased with, desire -- X any at all, (have, take) delight, desire, favour, like, move, be (well) pleased, have pleasure, will, would.

column8: delight in, desire, favor, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish
column9: From (H2654) chaphets; pleased with -- delight in, desire, favour, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish. see HEBREW (H2654) chaphets

column8: acceptable, delightsome, desire, things desired, matter, pleasant, purpose
column9: From (H2654) chaphets; pleasure; hence (abstractly) desire; concretely, a valuable thing; hence (by extension) a matter (as something in mind) -- acceptable, delight(-some), desire, things desired, matter, pleasant(-ure), purpose, willingly. see HEBREW (H2654) chaphets

column7: my delight is in her, a name for Zion, also the mother of King Manasseh
column9: From (H2656) chephets with suffixes; my delight (is) in her; Cheptsi-bah, a fanciful name for Palestine -- Hephzi-bah. see HEBREW (H2656) chephets
A primitive root; properly, to pry into; by implication, to delve, to explore -- dig, paw, search out, seek.

column8: be ashamed, be confounded, come be put to shame, bring reproach
column9: A primitive root (perhaps rath. The same as (H2658) chaphar through the idea of detection): to blush; figuratively, to be ashamed, disappointed; causatively, to shame, reproach -- be ashamed, be confounded, be brought to confusion (unto shame), come (be put to) shame, bring reproach. see HEBREW (H2658) chaphar

column4: proper name, masculine ; proper name, of a location
column9: From (H2658) chaphar or (H2659) chapher; a pit of shame; Chepher, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites -- Hepher. see HEBREW (H2658) chaphar see HEBREW (H2659) chapher

From (H2658) chaphar; a hole; only in connection with (H6512) perah, which ought rather to be joined as one word, thus chapharperah {khaf-ar- pay-raw'}; by reduplication from (H2658) chaphar; a burrower, i.e. Probably a rat -- + mole. see HEBREW (H2658) chaphar see HEBREW (H6512) perah see HEBREW (H2658) chaphar
Patronymically from (H2660) Chepher; a Chephrite (collectively) or descendants of Chepher -- Hepherites. see HEBREW (H2660) Chepher
Dual of (H2660) Chepher; double pit; Chapharajim, a place in Palestine -- Haphraim. see HEBREW (H2660) Chepher

column8: change, make diligent search, disguise self, hide, search for, out
column9: A primitive root; to seek; causatively, to conceal oneself (i.e. Let be sought), or mask -- change, (make) diligent (search), disquise self, hide, search (for, out).
From (H2664) chaphas; something covert, i.e. A trick -- search. see HEBREW (H2664) chaphas
A primitive root; to spread loose; figuratively, to manumit -- be free.
From (H2666) chaphash; something spread loosely, i.e. A carpet -- precious. see HEBREW (H2666) chaphash
From (H2666) chaphash; liberty (from slavery) -- freedom. see HEBREW (H2666) chaphash
And chophshiyth {khof-sheeth'}; from (H2666) chaphash; prostration by sickness (with (H1004) bayith, a hospital) -- several. see HEBREW (H2666) chaphash see HEBREW (H1004) bayith
From (H2666) chaphash; exempt (from bondage, tax or care) -- free, liberty. see HEBREW (H2666) chaphash

column8: archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound
column9: From (H2686) chatsats; properly, a piercer, i.e. An arrow; by implication, a wound; figuratively, (of God) thunder-bolt; (by interchange for (H6086) ets) the shaft of a spear -- + archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound. see HEBREW (H2686) chatsats see HEBREW (H6086) ets

column8: cut, dig, divide, grave, hew out made, mason
column9: Or chatseb {khaw-tsabe'}; a primitive root; to cut or carve (wood), stone or other material); by implication, to hew, split, square, quarry, engrave -- cut, dig, divide, grave, hew (out, -er), made, mason.

column8: divide, live out half, reach to the midst, participle
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2086) zed)); to cut or split in two; to halve -- divide, X live out half, reach to the midst, participle see HEBREW (H2086) zed

column7: the name of several places in Palestine, also one in Arabia
column9: A collective form of (H2691) chatser; village; Chatsor, the name (thus simply) of two places in Palestine and of one in Arabia -- Hazor. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser

column7: a place in the desert of Judah
column8: Hazor, Hadattah as if two places
column9: From (H2674) Chatsowr and a Aramaizing form of the feminine of (H2319) chadash (compare (H2323) chadath); new Chatsor, a place in Palestine -- Hazor, Hadattah (as if two places). see HEBREW (H2674) Chatsowr see HEBREW (H2323) chadath
From (H2673) chatsah; the middle (of the night) -- mid(-night). see HEBREW (H2673) chatsah

column8: half, middle, midnight, midst, part, two parts
column9: From (H2673) chatsah; the half or middle -- half, middle, mid(-night), midst, part, two parts. see HEBREW (H2673) chatsah
Or chetsiy {chay-tsee'}; prolongation from (H2671) chets; an arrow -- arrow. see HEBREW (H2671) chets

column7: Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth, an Israelite -- half of the Manahethites
column8: Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth, an Israelite -- half of the Manahethites
column9: From (H2677) chetsiy and the plural of (H4496) mnuwchah, with the article interposed; midst of the resting- places; Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth, an Israelite -- half of the Manahethites. see HEBREW (H2677) chetsiy see HEBREW (H4496) mnuwchah

column7: Chatsi-ham-Menachtite or descendant of Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth -- half of the Manahethites
column8: Chatsi-ham-Menachtite or descendant of Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth -- half of the Manahethites
column9: Patronymically from (H2679) Chatsiy ham-Mnuchowth; a Chatsi-ham-Menachtite or descendant of Chatsi-ham-Menuchoth -- half of the Manahethites. see HEBREW (H2679) Chatsiy ham-Mnuchowth
A collateral form of (H2691) chatser; a court or abode -- court. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser
Perhaps originally the same as (H2681) chatsiyr, from the greenness of a courtyard; grass; also a leek (collectively) -- grass, hay, herb, leek. see HEBREW (H2681) chatsiyr
From an unused root meaning to hold firmly; the bosom (as comprised between the arms) -- bosom.
A collateral form of (H2683) chetsen, and meaning the same -- arm, lap. see HEBREW (H2683) chetsen
(Aramaic) a primitive root; properly, to shear or cut close; figuratively, to be severe -- hasty, be urgent.

column8: archer, bands, cut off in the midst
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2673) chatsah); properly, to chop into, pierce or sever; hence, to curtail, to distribute (into ranks); as denom. From (H2671) chets, to shoot an arrow -- archer, X bands, cut off in the midst. see HEBREW (H2673) chatsah see HEBREW (H2671) chets
From (H2687) chatsats; properly, something cutting; hence, gravel (as grit); also (like (H2671) chets) an arrow -- arrow, gravel (stone). see HEBREW (H2687) chatsats see HEBREW (H2671) chets

column7: a place on the west side of the Dead Sea
column9: Or Chatsatson Tamar {khats-ats-one' taw-mawr'}; from (H2686) chatsats and (H8558) tamar; division (i.e. Perhaps row) of (the) palm-tree; Chatsetson-tamar, a place in Palestine -- Hazezon- tamar. see HEBREW (H2686) chatsats see HEBREW (H8558) tamar
By reduplication from (H2690) chatsar; a trumpet (from its sundered or quavering note) -- trumpet(-er). see HEBREW (H2690) chatsar

A primitive root; properly, to surround with a stockade, and thus separate from the open country; but used only in the reduplicated form chatsotser {khast-o-tsare'}; or (2 Chronicles 5:12) chatsorer {khats-o-rare'}; as dem. From (H2689) chatsotsrah; to trumpet, i.e. Blow on that instrument -- blow, sound, trumpeter. see HEBREW (H2689) chatsotsrah

(masculine and feminine); from (H2690) chatsar in its original sense; a yard (as inclosed by a fence); also a hamlet (as similarly surrounded with walls) -- court, tower, village. see HEBREW (H2690) chatsar

column7: a place on the S. border of Canaan
column9: From (H2691) chatser and (H146) 'Addar; (the) village of Addar; Chatsar-Addar, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-addar. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H146) 'Addar
From (H2691) chatser and a feminine of (H1408) Gad; (the) village of (female) Fortune; Chatsar-Gaddah, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-gaddah. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H1408) Gad

column7: a place near the border of Hauran
column9: From (H2691) chatser and (H8484) tiykown with the article interposed; village of the middle; Chatsar-hat-Tikon, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-hatticon. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H8484) tiykown
By an orthographical variation for (H2696) Chetsrown; enclosure; Chetsro, an Israelite -- Hezro, Hezrai. see HEBREW (H2696) Chetsrown

column4: proper name, of a location and person; proper name, masculine
column7: two Israelites, also two places in Judah
column9: From (H2691) chatser; court-yard; Chetsron, the name of a place in Palestine; also of two Israelites -- Hezron. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser
Patronymically from (H2696) Chetsrown; a Chetsronite or (collectively) descendants of Chetsron -- Hezronites. see HEBREW (H2696) Chetsrown
Feminine plural of (H2691) chatser; yards; Chatseroth, a place in Palestine -- Hazeroth. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser
Plural masculine of (H2691) chatser; yards; Chatserim, a place in Palestine -- Hazerim. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a territory
column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc
column9: From (H2691) chatser and (H4194) maveth; village of death; Chatsarmaveth, a place in Arabia -- Hazarmaveth. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H4194) maveth

column7: village of cavalry, a place in Simeon
column9: From (H2691) chatser and (H5484) cuwcah; village of cavalry; Chatsar-Susah, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-susah. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H5484) cuwcah

column7: village of horses, a place in Simeon
column9: From (H2691) chatser and the plural of (H5483) cuwc; village of horses; Chatsar-Susim, a place in Palestine -- Hazar- susim. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc

column7: a place on the N.E. border of Canaan
column9: From (H2691) chatser and a derivative of (H5869) ayin; village of springs; Chatsar-Enon, a place in Palestine -- Hazar- enon. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H5869) ayin

column7: a place on the N.E. border of Canaan
column9: From (H2691) chatser and the same as (H5881) Eynan; village of springs; Chatsar-Enan, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-enan. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H5881) Eynan

column7: village of the fox, a place in S. Judah
column9: From (H2691) chatser and (H7776) shuw'al; village of (the) fox; Chatsar-Shual, a place in Palestine -- Hazar-shual. see HEBREW (H2691) chatser see HEBREW (H7776) shuw'al

column7: something prescribed or owed, a statute
column8: appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decreed, due, law,
column9: From (H2710) chaqaq; an enactment; hence, an appointment (of time, space, quantity, labor or usage) -- appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decree(-d), due, law, measure, X necessary, ordinance(- nary), portion, set time, statute, task. see HEBREW (H2710) chaqaq

column8: carved work, portrayed, set a print
column9: A primitive root; to carve; by implication, to delineate; also to entrench -- carved work, portrayed, set a print.

column8: appointed, custom, manner, ordinance, site, statute
column9: Feminine of (H2706) choq, and meaning substantially the same -- appointed, custom, manner, ordinance, site, statute. see HEBREW (H2706) choq
From an unused root probably meaning to bend; crooked; Chakupha, one of the Nethinim -- Hakupha.

column8: appoint, decree, governor, grave, lawgiver, note, portray, print,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to hack, i.e. Engrave (Judges 5:14, to be a scribe simply); by implication, to enact (laws being cut in stone or metal tablets in primitive times) or (gen.) Prescribe -- appoint, decree, governor, grave, lawgiver, note, pourtray, print, set.
From (H2710) chaqaq; an enactment, a resolution -- decree, thought. see HEBREW (H2710) chaqaq
Or (fully) Chuwqoq {khoo-koke'}; from (H2710) chaqaq; appointed; Chukkok or Chukok, a place in Palestine -- Hukkok, Hukok. see HEBREW (H2710) chaqaq

column8: find out, make search out, seek out, sound, try
column9: A primitive root; properly, to penetrate; hence, to examine intimately -- find out, (make) search (out), seek (out), sound, try.

column7: a searching, a thing (to be) searched out
column9: From (H2713) chaqar; examination, enumeration, deliberation -- finding out, number, (un-)search(-able, -ed, out, -ing). see HEBREW (H2713) chaqar

Or (fully) chowr {khore}; from (H2787) charar; properly, white or pure (from the cleansing or shining power of fire (compare (H2751) choriy); hence (figuratively) noble (in rank) -- noble. see HEBREW (H2787) charar see HEBREW (H2751) choriy
From an unused (and vulgar) root probably meaning to evacuate the bowels: excrement; -dung. Also chariy {khar-ee'}.

column7: to be dry or dried up
column8: decay, be desolate, destroyer, be dry up, slay, surely, lay, lie,
column9: Or chareb {khaw-rabe'}; a primitive root; to parch (through drought) i.e. (by analogy,) to desolate, destroy, kill -- decay, (be) desolate, destroy(-er), (be) dry (up), slay, X surely, (lay, lie, make) waste.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to (H2717) charab; to demolish -- destroy. see HEBREW (H2717) charab

column8: axe, dagger, knife, mattock, sword, tool
column9: From (H2717) charab; drought; also a cutting instrument (from its destructive effect), as a knife, sword, or other sharp implement -- axe, dagger, knife, mattock, sword, tool. see HEBREW (H2717) charab
From (H2717) charab; parched or ruined -- desolate, dry, waste. see HEBREW (H2717) charab

column8: desolation, drought, dry, heat, utterly, waste
column9: A collaterally form of (H2719) chereb; drought or desolation -- desolation, drought, dry, heat, X utterly, waste. see HEBREW (H2719) chereb
From (H2717) charab; desolate; Choreb, a (generic) name for the Sinaitic mountains -- Horeb. see HEBREW (H2717) charab

column8: decayed place, desolate place destruction, laid waste place
column9: Feminine of (H2721) choreb; properly, drought, i.e. (by implication) a desolation -- decayed place, desolate (place, -tion), destruction, (laid) waste (place). see HEBREW (H2721) choreb
Feminine of (H2720) chareb; a desert -- dry (ground, land). see HEBREW (H2720) chareb
From (H2717) charab; parching heat -- drought. see HEBREW (H2717) charab
Or Charbownah {khar-bo-naw'}; of Persian origin; Charbona or Charbonah, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Harbona, Harbonah.
A primitive root; properly, to leap suddenly, i.e. (by implication) to be dismayed -- be afraid.
From (H2727) charag; the leaping insect, i.e. A locust -- beetle. see HEBREW (H2727) charag

column8: be make afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray away, quake, tremble
column9: A primitive root; to shudder with terror; hence, to fear; also to hasten (with anxiety) -- be (make) afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray (away), quake, tremble.
From (H2729) charad; fearful; also reverential -- afraid, trembling. see HEBREW (H2729) charad
Feminine of (H2730) chared; fear, anxiety -- care, X exceedingly, fear, quaking, trembling. see HEBREW (H2730) chared

column7: a place in the S. desert
column9: The same as (H2731) charadah; Charadah, a place in the Desert -- Haradah. see HEBREW (H2731) charadah
Patrial from a derivative of (H2729) charad (compare (H5878) Eyn Charod); a Charodite, or inhabitant of Charod -- Harodite. see HEBREW (H2729) charad see HEBREW (H5878) Eyn Charod

column7: to burn or be kindled with anger
column8: be angry, burn, be displeased, earnestly, fret self, grieve, be wax hot, be incensed,
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2787) charar); to glow or grow warm; figuratively (usually) to blaze up, of anger, zeal, jealousy -- be angry, burn, be displeased, X earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, X very, be wroth. See (H8474) tacharah. see HEBREW (H2787) charar see HEBREW (H8474) tacharah

column7: hollow of Gidgad, a place in the S. desert
column9: From (H2356) chowr and a collateral (masculine) form of (H1412) Gudgodah, with the article interposed; hole of the cleft: Chor-hag-Gidgad, a place in the Desert -- Hor-hagidgad. see HEBREW (H2356) chowr see HEBREW (H1412) Gudgodah
; from (H2734) charah and (H3050) Yahh; fearing Jah; Charhajah, an Israelite -- Harhaiah. see HEBREW (H2734) charah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From an unused root meaning to perforate; properly, pierced, i.e. A bead of pearl, gems or jewels (as strung) -- chain.
Or (shortened) charul {khaw-rool'}; apparently, a passive participle of an unused root probably meaning to be prickly; properly, pointed, i.e. A bramble or other thorny weed: nettle.
From passive participle of (H2763) charam and (H639) 'aph; snub-nosed; Charumaph, an Israelite -- Harumaph. see HEBREW (H2763) charam see HEBREW (H639) 'aph

column8: sore displeasure, fierceness, fury, fierce wrathful
column9: Or (shortened) charon {khaw-rone'}; from (H2734) charah; a burning of anger -- sore displeasure, fierce(-ness), fury, (fierce) wrath(-ful). see HEBREW (H2734) charah
A patrial from (probably) a collateral form of (H2756) Chariyph; a Charuphite or inhabitant of Charuph (or Chariph) -- Haruphite. see HEBREW (H2756) Chariyph

column8: decision, diligent, fine gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall
column9: Or charuts {khaw-roots'}; passive participle of (H2782) charats; properly, incised or (active) incisive; hence (as noun masculine or feminine) a trench (as dug), gold (as mined), a threshing-sledge (having sharp teeth); (figuratively) determination; also eager -- decision, diligent, (fine) gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall. see HEBREW (H2782) charats
The same as (H2742) charuwts; earnest; Charuts, an Israelite -- Haruz. see HEBREW (H2742) charuwts
A fuller form of (H2746) charchur; inflammation; Charchur, one of the Nethinim -- Harhur. see HEBREW (H2746) charchur
From the same as (H2775) cherec; perhaps shining; Charchas, an Israelite -- Harhas. see HEBREW (H2775) cherec
From (H2787) charar; fever (as hot); -extreme burning. see HEBREW (H2787) charar
From a primitive root meaning to engrave; a chisel or graver; also a style for writing -- graving tool, pen.
From the same as (H2747) cheret; a horoscopist (as drawing magical lines or circles) -- magician. see HEBREW (H2747) cheret
(Aramaic) the same as (H2748) chartom -- magician. see HEBREW (H2748) chartom
From (H2734) charah; a burning (i.e. Intense) anger -- fierce, X great, heat. see HEBREW (H2734) charah
From the same as (H2353) chuwr; white bread -- white. see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr

column7: inhab. of Edom, also the name of an Edomite, also the name of a Simeonite
column9: From (H2356) chowr; cave-dweller or troglodyte; a Chorite or aboriginal Idumaean -- Horims, Horites. see HEBREW (H2356) chowr
Or Chowriy {kho-ree'}; the same as (H2752) Choriy; Chori, the name of two men -- Hori. see HEBREW (H2752) Choriy
Or charit {khaw-reet'}; from the same as (H2747) cheret; properly, cut out (or hollow), i.e. (by implication) a pocket -- bag, crisping pin. see HEBREW (H2747) cheret

From the plural of (H2716) chere' and the plural of (H3123) yownah; excrements of doves {or perhaps rather the plural of a single word charapyown {khar-aw-yone'}; of similar or uncertain derivation, probably a kind of vegetable -- doves' dung. see HEBREW (H2716) chere' see HEBREW (H3123) yownah
From (H2778) charaph.; autumnal; Chariph, the name of two Israelites -- Hariph. see HEBREW (H2778) charaph.

column7: a cut, thing cut, sharp instrument
column9: Or charits {khaw-reets'}; from (H2782) charats; properly, incisure or (passively) incised (compare (H2742) charuwts); hence, a threshing-sledge (with sharp teeth): also a slice (as cut) -- + cheese, harrow. see HEBREW (H2782) charats see HEBREW (H2742) charuwts
From (H2790) charash; ploughing or its season -- earing (time), ground. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
From (H2790) charash in the sense of silence; quiet, i.e. Sultry (as feminine noun, the sirocco or hot east wind) -- vehement. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
A primitive root; to braid (i.e. To entangle or snare) or catch (game) in a net -- roast.
(Aramaic) a root probably allied to the equivalent of (H2787) charar; to scorch -- singe. see HEBREW (H2787) charar
From (H2760) charak; properly, a net, i.e. (by analogy) lattice -- lattice. see HEBREW (H2760) charak

column8: make accursed, consecrate, utterly destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly slay
column9: A primitive root; to seclude; specifically (by a ban) to devote to religious uses (especially destruction); physical and reflexive, to be blunt as to the nose -- make accursed, consecrate, (utterly) destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly (slay, make away).

column8: accursed dedicated thing, appointed to utter destruction, Extermination
column9: Or (Zecheriah 14:11) cherem {kheh'-rem}; from (H2763) charam; physical (as shutting in) a net (either literally or figuratively); usually a doomed object; abstr. Extermination -- (ac-)curse(-d, -d thing), dedicated thing, things which should have been utterly destroyed, (appointed to) utter destruction, devoted (thing), net. see HEBREW (H2763) charam
From (H2763) charam; devoted; Chorem, a place in Palestine -- Horem. see HEBREW (H2763) charam

column7: consecrated, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H2763) charam; snub-nosed; Charim, an Israelite -- Harim. see HEBREW (H2763) charam
From (H2763) charam; devoted; Chormah, a place in Palestine -- Hormah. see HEBREW (H2763) charam

column7: sacred (mountain), a mountain in S. Aram (Syria) and Northern Israel
column9: From (H2763) charam; abrupt; Chermon, a mount of Palestine -- Hermon. see HEBREW (H2763) charam
Plural of (H2768) Chermown; Hermons, i.e. Its peaks -- the Hermonites. see HEBREW (H2768) Chermown
From (H2763) charam; a sickle (as cutting) -- sickle. see HEBREW (H2763) charam

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: crossroads, a city in N. Mesopotamia
column9: From (H2787) charar; parched; Charan, the name of a man and also of a place -- Haran. see HEBREW (H2787) charar
Patrial from (H2773) Choronayim; a Choronite or inhabitant of Choronaim -- Horonite. see HEBREW (H2773) Choronayim

column7: two hollows, a place in Moab
column9: Dual of a derivative from (H2356) chowr; double cave-town; Choronajim, a place in Moab -- Horonaim. see HEBREW (H2356) chowr
Of uncertain derivation; Charnepher, an Israelite -- Harnepher.

Or (with a directive enclitic) charcah (khar'- saw}; from an unused root meaning to scrape; the itch; also (perhaps from the mediating idea of (H2777) charcuwth) the sun -- itch, sun. see HEBREW (H2777) charcuwth

column7: a mountain East of the Jordan, also dwelling place of the Amorites
column9: The same as (H2775) cherec; shining; Cheres, a mountain in Palestine -- Heres. see HEBREW (H2775) cherec
From (H2775) cherec (apparently in the sense of a red tile used for scraping); a potsherd, i.e. (by implication) a pottery; the name of a gate at Jerusalem -- east. see HEBREW (H2775) cherec

column8: betroth, blaspheme, defy, rail, reproach, upbraid
column9: A primitive root; to pull off, i.e. (by implication) to expose (as by stripping); specifically, to betroth (as if a surrender); figuratively, to carp at, i.e. Defame; denominative (from (H2779) choreph) to spend the winter -- betroth, blaspheme, defy, jeopard, rail, reproach, upbraid. see HEBREW (H2779) choreph
From (H2778) charaph.; properly, the crop gathered, i.e. (by implication) the autumn (and winter) season; figuratively, ripeness of age -- cold, winter (-house), youth. see HEBREW (H2778) charaph.
From (H2778) charaph.; reproachful; Chareph, an Israelite -- Hareph. see HEBREW (H2778) charaph.
From (H2778) charaph.; contumely, disgrace, the pudenda -- rebuke, reproach(-fully), shame. see HEBREW (H2778) charaph.

column8: bestir self, decide, decree, determine, maim, move
column9: A primitive root; properly, to point sharply, i.e. (literally) to wound; figuratively, to be alert, to decide -- bestir self, decide, decree, determine, maim, move.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2782) charats in the sense of vigor; the loin (as the seat of strength) -- loin. see HEBREW (H2782) charats
Of uncertain derivation; a fetter; figuratively, a pain -- band.
From (H2782) charats; a sour grape (as sharp in taste) -- kernel. see HEBREW (H2782) charats
A primitive root; to grate the teeth -- gnash.

column7: to be hot or scorched, to burn
column9: A primitive root; to glow, i.e. Literally (to melt, burn, dry up) or figuratively (to show or incite passion -- be angry, burn, dry, kindle.
From (H2787) charar; arid -- parched place. see HEBREW (H2787) charar
A collateral form mediating between (H2775) cherec and (H2791) cheresh; a piece of pottery -- earth(-en), (pot-)sherd, + stone. see HEBREW (H2775) cherec see HEBREW (H2791) cheresh

column7: to cut in, engrave, plow, devise
column8: altogether, cease, conceal, be deaf, devise, ear, graven, imagine,
column9: A primitive root; to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to engrave, plough; hence (from the use of tools) to fabricate (of any material); figuratively, to devise (in a bad sense); hence (from the idea of secrecy) to be silent, to let alone; hence (by implication) to be deaf (as an accompaniment of dumbness) -- X altogether, cease, conceal, be deaf, devise, ear, graven, imagine, leave off speaking, hold peace, plow(-er, man), be quiet, rest, practise secretly, keep silence, be silent, speak not a word, be still, hold tongue, worker.
From (H2790) charash; magical craft; also silence -- cunning, secretly. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
The same as (H2791) cheresh -- Cheresh, a Levite -- Heresh. see HEBREW (H2791) cheresh
From (H2790) charash; a forest (perhaps as furnishing the material for fabric) -- bough, forest, shroud, wood. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
Active participle of (H2790) charash; a fabricator or mechanic -- artificer. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
From (H2790) charash; deaf (whether literally or spir.) -- deaf. see HEBREW (H2790) charash

column8: artificer, carpenter, craftsman, engraver, maker, mason, skilful, smith,
column9: From (H2790) charash; a fabricator or any material -- artificer, (+) carpenter, craftsman, engraver, maker, + mason, skilful, (+) smith, worker, workman, such as wrought. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
From (H2792) Cheresh; magician; Charsha, one of the Nethinim -- Harsha. see HEBREW (H2792) Cheresh
Plural of (H2796) charash; mechanics, the name of a valley in Jerusalem -- Charashim, craftsmen. see HEBREW (H2796) charash
From (H2790) charash; mechanical work -- carving, cutting. see HEBREW (H2790) charash
The same as (H2799) charosheth; Charosheth, a place in Palestine -- Harosheth. see HEBREW (H2799) charosheth
A primitive root; to engrave -- graven.
From (H2801) charath (but equivalent to (H2793) choresh); forest; Chereth, a thicket in Palestine -- Hereth. see HEBREW (H2801) charath see HEBREW (H2793) choresh

column8: make account of, conceive, consider, count, cunning man, work, workman, devise,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to plait or interpenetrate, i.e. (literally) to weave or (gen.) To fabricate; figuratively, to plot or contrive (usually in a malicious sense); hence (from the mental effort) to think, regard, value, compute -- (make) account (of), conceive, consider, count, cunning (man, work, workman), devise, esteem, find out, forecast, hold, imagine, impute, invent, be like, mean, purpose, reckon(-ing be made), regard, think.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2803) chashab; to regard -- repute. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab
From (H2803) chashab; a belt or strap (as being interlaced) -- curious girdle. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab
From (H2803) chashab and (H1777) diyn; considerate judge; Chasbaddanah, an Israelite -- Hasbadana. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab see HEBREW (H1777) diyn
From (H2803) chashab; estimation; Cashubah, an Israelite -- Hashubah. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab
From (H2803) chashab; properly, contrivance; by implication, intelligence -- account, device, reason. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab

column7: a place East of the Jordan
column9: The same as (H2808) cheshbown; Cheshbon, a place East of the Jordan -- Heshbon. see HEBREW (H2808) cheshbown
From (H2803) chashab; a contrivance, i.e. Actual (a warlike machine) or mental (a machination) -- engine, invention. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab

column7: Yah has taken account, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Chashabyahuw {khash-ab-yaw'-hoo}; from (H2803) chashab and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has regarded; Chashabjah, the name of nine Israelites -- Hashabiah. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: an Israelite leader in Nehemiah\'s time
column9: Feminine of (H2808) cheshbown; inventiveness; Chashnah, an Israelite -- Hashabnah. see HEBREW (H2808) cheshbown
From (H2808) cheshbown and (H3050) Yahh; thought of Jah; Chashabnejah, the name of two Israelites -- Hashabniah. see HEBREW (H2808) cheshbown see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to be silent, inactive, or still
column8: hold peace, keep silence, be silent, be still
column9: A primitive root; to hush or keep quiet -- hold peace, keep silence, be silent, (be) still.
From (H2803) chashab; intelligent; Chashshub, the name of two or three Israelites -- Hashub, Hasshub. see HEBREW (H2803) chashab
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2821) chashak; the dark -- darkness. see HEBREW (H2821) chashak
Or Chasuphao {khas-oo-faw'}; from (H2834) chasaph; nakedness; Chasupha, one of the Nethinim -- Hashupha, Hasupha. see HEBREW (H2834) chasaph

(Aramaic) a collateral root to one corresponding to (H2363) chuwsh in the sense of readiness; to be necessary (from the idea of convenience) or (transitively) to need -- careful, have need of. see HEBREW (H2363) chuwsh
From a root corresponding to (H2818) chashach; necessity -- be needful. see HEBREW (H2818) chashach

column8: assuage, darken, forbear, hinder, hold back, keep back, punish, refrain,
column9: A primitive root; to restrain or (reflex.) Refrain; by implication, to refuse, spare, preserve; also (by interch. With (H2821) chashak) to observe -- assuage, X darken, forbear, hinder, hold back, keep (back), punish, refrain, reserve, spare, withhold. see HEBREW (H2821) chashak

column8: be black, be make dark, darken, cause darkness, be dim, hide
column9: A primitive root; to be dark (as withholding light); transitively, to darken -- be black, be (make) dark, darken, cause darkness, be dim, hide.
From (H2821) chashak; the dark; hence (literally) darkness; figuratively, misery, destruction, death, ignorance, sorrow, wickedness -- dark(-ness), night, obscurity. see HEBREW (H2821) chashak
From (H2821) chashak; dark (figuratively, i.e. Obscure) -- meaning see HEBREW (H2821) chashak
From (H2821) chashak; darkness -- dark. see HEBREW (H2821) chashak
Or chashekah {khash-ay-kaw'}; from (H2821) chashak; darkness; figuratively, misery -- darkness. see HEBREW (H2821) chashak
A primitive root; to make (intrans. Be) unsteady, i.e. Weak -- feeble.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to (H2826) chashal; to weaken, i.e. Crush -- subdue. see HEBREW (H2826) chashal
From the same as (H2831) chashman; enriched; Chashum, the name of two or three Israelites -- Hashum. see HEBREW (H2831) chashman
The same as (H2831) chashman; opulent; Cheshmon, a place in Palestine -- Heshmon. see HEBREW (H2831) chashman
Of uncertain derivation; probably bronze or polished spectrum metal -- amber.
From an unused root (probably meaning firm or capacious in resources); apparently wealthy -- princes.

column7: a place in the S. desert
column9: Feminine of (H2831) chashman; fertile; Chasmonah, a place in the Desert -- Hashmonah. see HEBREW (H2831) chashman
From an unused root probably meaning to contain or sparkle; perhaps a pocket (as holding the Urim and Thummim), or rich (as containing gems), used only of the gorget of the highpriest -- breastplate.

column7: to strip off, strip, make bare
column8: make bare, clean, discover, draw out, take, uncover
column9: A primitive root; to strip off, i.e. Generally to make naked (for exertion or in disgrace), to drain away or bail up (a liquid) -- make bare, clean, discover, draw out, take, uncover.
From (H2834) chasaph; properly, drawn off, i.e. Separated; hence, a small company (as divided from the rest) -- little flock. see HEBREW (H2834) chasaph

column8: have a delight, have a desire, fillet, long, set in love
column9: A primitive root; to cling, i.e. Join, (figuratively) to love, delight in; elliptically (or by interchangeable for (H2820) chasak) to deliver -- have a delight, (have a) desire, fillet, long, set (in) love. see HEBREW (H2820) chasak
From (H2836) chashaq; delight -- desire, pleasure. see HEBREW (H2836) chashaq
Or chashuwq {khaw-shook'}; past participle of (H2836) chashaq; attached, i.e. A fence-rail or rod connecting the posts or pillars -- fillet. see HEBREW (H2836) chashaq
From (H2836) chashaq; conjoined, i.e. A wheel-spoke or rod connecting the hub with the rim -- felloe. see HEBREW (H2836) chashaq
From an unused root meaning to bind together; combined, i.e. The nave or hub of a wheel (as holding the spokes together) -- spoke.
From the same as (H2840) chishshur; properly, a combination or gathering, i.e. Of watery clouds -- dark. see HEBREW (H2840) chishshur
By variation for (H7179) qash; dry grass -- chaff. see HEBREW (H7179) qash
Patronymically from (H2364) Chuwshah; a Chushathite or descendant of Chushah -- Hushathite. see HEBREW (H2364) Chuwshah
From (H2865) chathath; concretely, crushed; also afraid; abstractly, terror -- broken, dismayed, dread, fear. see HEBREW (H2865) chathath

column7: a son of Canaan and probably ancestor of the Hittites
column9: From (H2865) chathath; terror; Cheth, an aboriginal Canaanite -- Heth. see HEBREW (H2865) chathath
A primitive root; to lay hold of; especially to pick up fire -- heap, take (away).
From (H2865) chathath; fear -- terror. see HEBREW (H2865) chathath
From (H2853) chathal; swathed, i.e. A bandage -- roller. see HEBREW (H2853) chathal
From (H2844) chath; terror -- fear. see HEBREW (H2844) chath
Patronymically from (H2845) Cheth; a Chittite, or descendant of Cheth -- Hittite, Hittities. see HEBREW (H2845) Cheth
From (H2865) chathath; fear -- terror. see HEBREW (H2865) chathath
A primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) to decree -- determine.
A primitive root; to swathe -- X at all, swaddle.
From (H2853) chathal; a swathing cloth (figuratively) -- swaddling band. see HEBREW (H2853) chathal
From (H2853) chathal; enswathed; Chethlon, a place in Palestine -- Hethlon. see HEBREW (H2853) chathal

column7: to seal, affix a seal, seal up
column8: make an end, mark, seal up, stop
column9: A primitive root; to close up; especially to seal -- make an end, mark, seal (up), stop.
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to (H2856) chatham; to seal -- seal. see HEBREW (H2856) chatham
Feminine active participle of (H2856) chatham; a seal -- signet. see HEBREW (H2856) chatham

column8: join in affinity, father-in-law, make marriages, mother-in-law, son-in-law
column9: A primitive root; to give (a daughter) away in marriage; hence (generally) to contract affinity by marriage -- join in affinity, father in law, make marriages, mother in law, son in law.

From (H2859) chathan; a relative by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively, a circumcised child (as a species of religious espousal) -- bridegroom, husband, son in law. see HEBREW (H2859) chathan
From (H2859) chathan; a wedding -- espousal. see HEBREW (H2859) chathan
A primitive root; to clutch -- take away.
From (H2862) chathaph; properly, rapine; figuratively, robbery -- prey. see HEBREW (H2862) chathaph
A primitive root; to force a passage, as by burglary; figuratively, with oars -- dig (through), row.

column8: abolish, affright, be make afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage
column9: A primitive root; properly, to prostrate; hence, to break down, either (literally) by violence, or (figuratively) by confusion and fear -- abolish, affright, be (make) afraid, amaze, beat down, discourage, (cause to) dismay, go down, scare, terrify.
From (H2865) chathath; dismay -- casting down. see HEBREW (H2865) chathath
The same as (H2866) chathath; Chathath, an Israelite -- cathath. see HEBREW (H2866) chathath
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to rejoice -- be glad.
(Aramaic) from (H2868) t'eb; the same as (H2896) towb; good -- fine, good. see HEBREW (H2868) t'eb see HEBREW (H2896) towb
From (H2895) towb and (H410) 'el; pleasing (to) God; Tabeel, the name of a Syrian and of a Persian -- Tabeal, Tabeel. see HEBREW (H2895) towb see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Passive participle of (H2881) tabal; properly, dyed, i.e. A turban (probably as of colored stuff) -- dyed attire. see HEBREW (H2881) tabal
From an unused root meaning to pile up; properly, accumulated; i.e. (by implication) a summit -- middle, midst.
A primitive root; to slaughter (animals or men) -- kill, (make) slaughter, slay.

From (H2873) tabach; properly, something slaughtered; hence, a beast (or meat, as butchered); abstr. Butchery (or concretely, a place of slaughter) -- X beast, slaughter, X slay, X sore. see HEBREW (H2873) tabach
The same as (H2874) tebach; massacre; Tebach, the name of a Mesopotamian and of an Israelite -- Tebah. see HEBREW (H2874) tebach

From (H2873) tabach; properly, a butcher; hence, a lifeguardsman (because he was acting as an executioner); also a cook (usually slaughtering the animal for food) -- cook, guard. see HEBREW (H2873) tabach
(Aramaic) the same as (H2876) tabbach; a lifeguardsman -- guard. see HEBREW (H2876) tabbach
Feminine of (H2874) tebach and meaning the same -- flesh, slaughter. see HEBREW (H2874) tebach
Feminine of (H2876) tabbach; a female cook -- cook. see HEBREW (H2876) tabbach
From (H2878) tibehah; slaughter; Tibchath, a place in Syria -- Tibhath. see HEBREW (H2878) tibehah
A primitive root; to dip, to immerse -- dip, plunge.
From (H2881) tabal and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has dipped; Tebaljah, an Israelite -- Tebaliah. see HEBREW (H2881) tabal see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; to sink -- drown, fasten, settle, sink.
Plural of (H2885) tabba'ath; rings; Tabbaoth, one of the Nethinim -- Tabaoth. see HEBREW (H2885) tabba'ath
From (H2883) taba'; properly, a seal (as sunk into the wax), i.e. Signet (for sealing); hence (generally) a ring of any kind -- ring. see HEBREW (H2883) taba'

column7: perhaps "Rimmon is good", father of Benhaddad, king of Aram (Syria)
column9: From (H2895) towb and (H7417) Rimmown; pleasing (to) Rimmon; Tabrimmon, a Syrian -- Tabrimmon. see HEBREW (H2895) towb see HEBREW (H7417) Rimmown
Probably of foreign derivation; Tebeth, the tenth Heb. Month -- Tebeth.

column7: a place of refuge of the Midianites
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Tabbath, a place East of the Jordan -- Tabbath.
Or tahor {taw-hore'}; from (H2891) taher; pure (in a physical, chemical, ceremonial or moral sense) -- clean, fair, pure(-ness). see HEBREW (H2891) taher
From (H2891) taher; purity -- pureness. see HEBREW (H2891) taher

column8: be make, make self, pronounce clean, cleanse self, purge
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be bright; i.e. (by implication) to be pure (physical sound, clear, unadulterated; Levitically, uncontaminated; morally, innocent or holy) -- be (make, make self, pronounce) clean, cleanse (self), purge, purify(-ier, self).
From (H2891) taher; literally brightness; ceremonially purification -- clearness, glory, purifying. see HEBREW (H2891) taher
Feminine of (H2892) tohar; ceremonial purification; moral purity -- X is cleansed, cleansing, purification(-fying). see HEBREW (H2892) tohar
A primitive root; to sweep away -- sweep.

column8: be do better, cheer, be do, seem good, make goodly, please, be, do,
column9: A primitive root, to be (transitively, do or make) good (or well) in the widest sense -- be (do) better, cheer, be (do, seem) good, (make) goodly, X please, (be, do, go, play) well.

column4: Adjective; verb; verb; feminine; noun masculine; noun feminine; noun feminine
column8: beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, fair word, be in favor,
column9: From (H2895) towb; good (as an adjective) in the widest sense; used likewise as a noun, both in the masculine and the feminine, the singular and the plural (good, a good or good thing, a good man or woman; the good, goods or good things, good men or women), also as an adverb (well) -- beautiful, best, better, bountiful, cheerful, at ease, X fair (word), (be in) favour, fine, glad, good (deed, -lier, -liest, -ly, -ness, -s), graciously, joyful, kindly, kindness, liketh (best), loving, merry, X most, pleasant, + pleaseth, pleasure, precious, prosperity, ready, sweet, wealth, welfare, (be) well ((-favoured)). see HEBREW (H2895) towb

column7: a region East of the Jordan
column9: The same as (H2896) towb; good; Tob, a region apparently East of the Jordan -- Tob. see HEBREW (H2896) towb

column8: fair, gladness, goodness, thing joy, go well with
column9: From (H2895) towb; good (as a noun), in the widest sense, especially goodness (superlative concretely, the best), beauty, gladness, welfare -- fair, gladness, good(-ness, thing, -s), joy, go well with. see HEBREW (H2895) towb

column7: good is my LORD, a Levite
column9: From (H2896) towb and (H138) 'Adoniyah; pleasing (to) Adonijah; Tob-Adonijah, an Israelite -- Tob-adonijah. see HEBREW (H2896) towb see HEBREW (H138) 'Adoniyah

column7: Yah is my good, three Israelites, also an Ammonite
column9: Or Towbiyahuw {to-bee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H2896) towb and (H3050) Yahh; goodness of Jehovah; Tobijah, the name of three Israelites and of one Samaritan -- Tobiah, Tobijah. see HEBREW (H2896) towb see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; to spin -- spin.
A primitive root; to smear, especially with lime -- daub, overlay, plaister, smut.
From an unusued root meaning to go around or bind; a fillet for the forehead -- frontlet.

column8: carry away, utterly cast down, forth, out, send out
column9: A primitive root; to pitch over or reel; hence (transitively) to cast down or out -- carry away, (utterly) cast (down, forth, out), send out.
From an unused root meaning to range in a regular manner; a row; hence, a wall -- row.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6697) tsuwr; a rock or hill -- mountain. see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr
A primitive root; to pounce as a bird of prey -- haste.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2901) tavah; hunger (as twisting) -- fasting. see HEBREW (H2901) tavah
A primitive root; to stretch a bow, as an archer -- (bow-)shot.

From (H2909) tachah (or (H2902) tuwach) in the sense of overlaying; (in the plural only) the kidneys (as being covered); hence (figuratively) the inmost thought -- inward parts. see HEBREW (H2909) tachah see HEBREW (H2902) tuwach
From (H2912) tachan; a hand mill; hence, a millstone -- to grind. see HEBREW (H2912) tachan
A primitive root; to grind meal; hence, to be a concubine (that being their employment) -- grind(-er).
From (H2912) tachan; a hand mill; hence (figuratively) chewing -- grinding. see HEBREW (H2912) tachan
From an unused root meaning to burn; a boil or ulcer (from the inflammation), especially a tumor in the anus or pudenda (the piles) -- emerod.
From (the equiv. Of) (H2902) tuwach; mortar or plaster -- daubing. see HEBREW (H2902) tuwach

From an unused root meaning apparently to be sticky (rath. Perb. A demon. From (H2894) tuw', through the idea of dirt to be swept away); mud or clay; figuratively, calamity -- clay, dirt, mire. see HEBREW (H2894) tuw'
(Aramaic) perhaps, by interchange, for a word corresponding to (H2916) tiyt; clay -- miry. see HEBREW (H2916) tiyt
Feminine of (an equivalent to) (H2905) tuwr; a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet -- (goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row. see HEBREW (H2905) tuwr
From (H2926) talal; dew (as covering vegetation) -- dew. see HEBREW (H2926) talal
(Aramaic) the same as (H2919) tal -- dew. see HEBREW (H2919) tal
A primitive root; properly, to cover with pieces; i.e. (by implication) to spot or variegate (as tapestry) -- clouted, with divers colours, spotted.
Apparently from (H2921) tala' in the (orig.) Sense of covering (for protection); a lamb (compare (H2924) taleh) -- lamb. see HEBREW (H2921) tala' see HEBREW (H2924) taleh

column7: a place where Saul mustered his forces
column9: From the plural of (H2922) tla'; lambs; Telaim, a place in Palestine -- Telaim. see HEBREW (H2922) tla'
By variation for (H2922) tla'; a lamb -- lamb. see HEBREW (H2922) tla'
From (H2904) tuwl; overthrow or rejection -- captivity. see HEBREW (H2904) tuwl
A primitive root; properly, to strew over, i.e. (by implication) to cover in or plate (with beams) -- cover.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2926) talal; to cover with shade -- have a shadow. see HEBREW (H2926) talal

column7: an Israelite, also a place in the desert of Judah
column9: From an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression; Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper -- Telem.
From the same as (H2728) chargol; oppressive; Talmon, a temple doorkeeper -- Talmon. see HEBREW (H2728) chargol

column8: defile self, pollute self, be make, make self, pronounce unclean, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated) -- defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, X utterly.
From (H2930) tame'; foul in a relig. Sense -- defiled, + infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean. see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
From (H2930) tame'; religious impurity -- filthiness, unclean(-ness). see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
A collateral form of (H2930) tame'; to be impure in a religious sense -- be defiled, be reputed vile. see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
A primitive root; to hide (by covering over) -- hide, lay privily, in secret.
From an unused root probably meaning to weave; a basket (of interlaced osiers) -- basket.
A primitive root; to soil -- defile.
A primitive root; to wander;,causatively to lead astray -- seduce.
A primitive root; to taste; figuratively, to perceive -- X but, perceive, taste.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2938) ta'am; to taste; causatively to feed -- make to eat, feed. see HEBREW (H2938) ta'am

column8: advice, behavior, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding
column9: From (H2938) ta'am; properly, a taste, i.e. (figuratively) perception; by implication, intelligence; transitively, a mandate -- advice, behaviour, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding. see HEBREW (H2938) ta'am

column7: account, to be commanded, commandment, matter
column8: account, to be commanded, commandment, matter
column9: (Aramaic) from (H2939) t'am; properly, a taste, i.e. (as in (H2940) ta'am) a judicial sentence -- account, X to be commanded, commandment, matter. see HEBREW (H2939) t'am see HEBREW (H2940) ta'am

column8: chancellor, command, commandment, decree, regard, taste, wisdom
column9: (Aramaic) from (H2939) t'am, and equivalent to (H2941) ta'am; properly, flavor; figuratively, judgment (both subjective and objective); hence, account (both subj. And obj.) -- + chancellor, + command, commandment, decree, + regard, taste, wisdom. see HEBREW (H2939) t'am see HEBREW (H2941) ta'am
A primitive root; to load a beast -- lade.
A primitive root; to stab -- thrust through.
From (H2952) taphaph (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children); a family (mostly used collectively in the singular) -- (little) children (ones), families. see HEBREW (H2952) taphaph

A primitive root; to flatten out or extend (as a tent); figuratively, to nurse a child (as promotive of growth); or perhaps a denom. From (H2947) tephach, from dandling on the palms -- span, swaddle. see HEBREW (H2947) tephach
From (H2946) taphach; a spread of the hand, i.e. A palm- breadth (not \"span\" of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm) -- coping, hand-breadth. see HEBREW (H2946) taphach
From (H2946) taphach (the same as (H2947) tephach) -- hand-breadth (broad). see HEBREW (H2946) taphach see HEBREW (H2947) tephach
From (H2946) taphach; nursing -- span long. see HEBREW (H2946) taphach

column7: to smear, plaster over, stick, glue
column9: A primitive root; properly, to stick on as a patch; figuratively, to impute falsely -- forge(-r), sew up.
Of foreign derivation; a military governor -- captain.

column7: to trip, take small quick steps
column9: A primitive root; apparently to trip (with short steps) coquettishly -- mince.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6852) tsaphar, and meaning the same as (H6856) tsipporen; a finger-nail; also a hoof or claw -- nail. see HEBREW (H6852) tsaphar see HEBREW (H6856) tsipporen
A primitive root; properly, apparently to be thick; figuratively, to be stupid -- be fat.
Probably from (H5197) nataph; a dropping (of ointment); Taphath, an Israelitess -- Taphath. see HEBREW (H5197) nataph
A primitive root; to drive on; figuratively, to follow close -- continual.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2956) tarad; to expel -- drive. see HEBREW (H2956) tarad
A variation of (H2962) terem; not yet -- before. see HEBREW (H2962) terem
A primitive root; to overburden -- weary.
From (H2959) tarach; a burden -- cumbrance, trouble. see HEBREW (H2959) tarach
From an unused root apparently meaning to be moist; properly, dripping; hence, fresh (i.e. Recently made such) -- new, putrefying.
From an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend; properly, non-occurrence; used adverbially, not yet or before -- before, ere, not yet.

column8: catch, without doubt, feed, rend in pieces, surely, tear in pieces
column9: A primitive root; to pluck off or pull to pieces; causatively to supply with food (as in morsels) -- catch, X without doubt, feed, ravin, rend in pieces, X surely, tear (in pieces).
From (H2963) taraph; something torn, i.e. A fragment, e.g. A fresh leaf, prey, food -- leaf, meat, prey, spoil. see HEBREW (H2963) taraph
From (H2963) taraph; recently torn off, i.e. Fresh -- pluckt off. see HEBREW (H2963) taraph
Feminine (collectively) of (H2964) tereph; prey, i.e. Flocks devoured by animals -- ravin, (that which was) torn (of beasts, in pieces). see HEBREW (H2964) tereph
(Aramaic) from a name of foreign derivation; a Tarpelite (collectively) or inhabitants of Tarpel, a place in Assyria -- Tarpelites.
A primitive root; to desire -- long.
A primitive root; to be suitable -- appertain.

column7: Yah hears, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Ya.azanyahuw {yah-az-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H238) 'azan and (H3050) Yahh; heard of Jah; Jaazanjah, the name of four Israelites -- Jaazaniah. Compare (H3153) Yzanyah. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3153) Yzanyah
From (H215) 'owr; enlightener; Jair, the name of four Israelites -- Jair. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr
Patronymically from (H2971) Ya'iyr; a Jairite or descendant of Jair -- Jairite. see HEBREW (H2971) Ya'iyr
A primitive root; properly, to be slack, i.e. (figuratively) to be foolish -- dote, be (become, do) foolish(-ly).

column7: to show willingness, be pleased, determine, undertake (to do anything)
column8: assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, willingly, would
column9: A primitive root (probably rather the same as (H2973) ya'al through the idea of mental weakness); properly, to yield, especially assent; hence (pos.) To undertake as an act of volition -- assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, X willingly, would. see HEBREW (H2973) ya'al

Of Egyptian origin; a channel, e.g. A fosse, canal, shaft; specifically the Nile, as the one river of Egypt, including its collateral trenches; also the Tigris, as the main river of Assyria -- brook, flood, river, stream.

column8: cause to despair, one that is desperate, be no hope
column9: A primitive root; to desist, i.e. (figuratively) to despond -- (cause to) despair, one that is desperate, be no hope.
Or {yo-she-yaw'-hoo}; from the same root as (H803) 'ashuwyah and (H3050) Yahh; founded of Jah; Joshijah, the name of two Israelites -- Josiah. see HEBREW (H803) 'ashuwyah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H857) 'athah; an entry -- entrance. see HEBREW (H857) 'athah
From the same as (H871) 'Athariym; stepping; Jeatherai, an Israelite -- Jeaterai. see HEBREW (H871) 'Athariym

column7: to cry in a shrill voice
column9: A primitive root; to bawl -- cry out.
From (H2986) yabal; produce, i.e. A crop or (figuratively) wealth -- fruit, increase. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H947) buwc; trodden, i.e. Threshing-place; Jebus, the aboriginal name of Jerusalem -- Jebus. see HEBREW (H947) buwc
Patrial from (H2982) Ybuwc; a Jebusite or inhabitant of Jebus -- Jebusite(-s). see HEBREW (H2982) Ybuwc

column7: He chooses, a son of David
column9: From (H977) bachar; choice; Jibchar, an Israelite -- Ibhar. see HEBREW (H977) bachar

column7: one who is intelligent, two Canaanite kings
column9: From (H995) biyn; intelligent; Jabin, the name of two Canaanitish kings -- Jabin. see HEBREW (H995) biyn
A primitive root; properly, to flow; causatively, to bring (especially with pomp) -- bring (forth), carry, lead (forth).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2986) yabal; to bring -- bring, carry. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H2986) yabal; a stream -- (water-)course, stream. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
The same as (H2988) yabal; Jabal, an antediluvian -- Jabal. see HEBREW (H2988) yabal
From (H2986) yabal; having running sores -- wen. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H1104) bala' and (H5971) am; devouring people; Jibleam, a place in Palestine -- Ibleam. see HEBREW (H1104) bala' see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: to perform the duty of a husband\'s brother
column8: perform the duty of a husband\'s brother, marry
column9: A primitive root of doubtful meaning; used only as a denominative from (H2993) yabam; to marry a (deceased) brother's widow -- perform the duty of a husband's brother, marry. see HEBREW (H2993) yabam
From (the orig. Of) (H2992) yabam; a brother-in-law -- husband's brother. see HEBREW (H2992) yabam
Feminine participle of (H2992) yabam; a sister-in-law -- brother's wife, sister in law. see HEBREW (H2992) yabam

column7: El causes to build, two cities in Isr
column9: From (H1129) banah and (H410) 'el: built of God; Jabneel, the name of two places in Palestine -- Jabneel. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: he causes to build, a Philistine city
column9: From (H1129) banah; a building; Jabneh, a place in Palestine -- Jabneh. see HEBREW (H1129) banah
From (H1129) banah and (H3050) Yahh; built of Jah; Jibnejah, an Israelite -- Ibneiah. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H1129) banah and (H3050) Yahh; building of Jah; Jibnijah, an Israelite -- Ibnijah. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: a river East of the Jordan
column9: Probably from (H1238) baqaq; pouring forth; Jabbok, a river east of the Jordan -- Jabbok. see HEBREW (H1238) baqaq

column7: Yah blesses, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H1288) barak and (H3050) Yahh: blessed of Jah; Jeberekjah, an Israelite -- Jeberechiah. see HEBREW (H1288) barak see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to be dry, dried up, or withered
column8: be ashamed, clean, be confounded, make dry up, do shamefully, utterly, wither away
column9: A primitive root; to be ashamed, confused or disappointed; also (as failing) to dry up (as water) or wither (as herbage) -- be ashamed, clean, be confounded, (make) dry (up), (do) shame(-fully), X utterly, wither (away).
